Company Overview of The Boston Company Asset Management, LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Boston Company Asset Management, LLC is a privately owned investment manager. The firm provides its services to individuals including high net worth individuals, banking and thrift institutions, investment companies, Taft-Hartley, endowments, foundations, pension and profit sharing plans, insurance companies, other investment advisers, pooled investment vehicles, charitable organizations, corporations, state or municipal government entities, insurance funds, non-U.S. mutual funds, health and welfare funds, and severance funds. It manages separate client focused equity and balanced portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity and fixed income mutual funds. It invests in the publi...
The Boston Company Asset Management, LLC is a privately owned investment manager. The firm provides its services to individuals including high net worth individuals, banking and thrift institutions, investment companies, Taft-Hartley, endowments, foundations, pension and profit sharing plans, insurance companies, other investment advisers, pooled investment vehicles, charitable organizations, corporations, state or municipal government entities, insurance funds, non-U.S. mutual funds, health and welfare funds, and severance funds. It manages separate client focused equity and balanced portfolios. The firm also launches and manages equity and fixed income mutual funds. It invests in the public equity markets across the globe. The firm also makes investments in ADRs and ETFs. It invests in growth and value stocks of small-cap, mid-cap, and large-cap companies. The firm also invests in stocks of dividend paying companies. It employs fundamental and quantitative analysis along with bottom-up stock picking approach to create its portfolios. The firm was founded on August 24, 1970 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts with additional offices in Los Angeles, California, Chicago, Illinois, Denver, Colorado, Greenwich, Connecticut, and New York City.
